{"TopicId":91441,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"[Solved] Orion MPCV Dimensions?","CreatedByName":"SpaceLaunchSystem","CreatedById":125698,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T02:14:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SpaceLaunchSystem","CreatedById":125698,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T02:14:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOriginal Post:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI want to model the Orion Crew Module, but I need the exterior dimensions. Wikipedia says \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orion_(spacecraft)#Crew_Module\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E that it is will be 5.02m in diameter and 3.3m tall with a side angle of 57.5\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00B0, but that would mean that the top would be 0.82m in diameter and when I model that in SketchUp, It dosen\u0027t exactly look like the renderings \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E.\u003Cp\u003EHere it is:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/lRMHl3J.png\u0022 alt=\u0022lRMHl3J.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT:\u003C/strong\u003E using a concept image and the Measure tool in GIMP, I\u0027ve determined that the actual angle is 60.19, meaning the top is 1.24m wide, but the hight doesn\u0027t look right. Here it is:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DZS4vRO.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022DZS4vRO.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWell, I (finally) found the dimensions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHere they are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EL/W (Base) = 5.02m\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EH = 2.62m\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EL/W (top) = 2.02m\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESide Angle = 60.19\u00C3\u201A\u00C2\u00B0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-11-28T18:09:34Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2014 06:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by SpaceLaunchSystem\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whirligig Girl","CreatedById":36077,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T02:19:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELooks pretty close to me. Oh, and remember that parts in KSP are around 64% real scale counterparts, unless using Realism Overhaul.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceLaunchSystem","CreatedById":125698,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T02:45:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIts shape dosen\u0027t look all that like the real thing when you compare my rough model to this render:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/80/Orion_with_ATV_SM.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022Orion_with_ATV_SM.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tygoo7","CreatedById":57345,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T02:51:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMaybe this picture might help with creating the shape, not really the dimensions though. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://images.spaceref.com/news/2013/mg2_Orion-SM_labels.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022mg2_Orion-SM_labels.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T05:48:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EPerhaps if you find the top diameter, you can put it into the equation for a truncated cone and solve for total height.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAll hail Algebra!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceLaunchSystem","CreatedById":125698,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-11-28T16:26:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tygoo7\u0022 data-cite=\u0022tygoo7\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EMaybe this picture might help with creating the shape, not really the dimensions though. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://images.spaceref.com/news/2013/mg2_Orion-SM_labels.jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://images.spaceref.com/news/2013/mg2_Orion-SM_labels.jpg\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAssuming the bottom diameter from Wikipedia is right, and using this picture, I think it may be possible to calculate the top\u0027s diameter! Yay for geometry!\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-11-28T16:35:31Z\u0022 title=\u002211/28/2014 04:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 28, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by SpaceLaunchSystem\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}